excerpt: Traditional indoor facility built in 1940 featuring merchants of produce, flowers & seafood.
detail_description: Mercado dos Lavradores, a traditional indoor market established in 1940, is a popular attraction in Funchal. It offers an array of goods including fresh produce, flowers, and seafood. Visitors can explore the vibrant fruit stands showcasing guavas, dragon fruits, and lychees while enjoying a drink at the Madeira Beer Lab. The market also features a bustling fish section and flower stalls where locals sell beautiful blooms in traditional attire.
name: Mercado dos Lavradores
address: Largo dos Lavradores, 9060-158 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Hillside botanical gardens with a bird park, natural history museum & glass houses, plus sea views.
detail_description: The Madeira Botanical Garden is a hillside paradise boasting a bird park, natural history museum, and glass houses with stunning sea views. This modern marvel of contemporary architecture, co-designed by renowned architects Abalos & Herreros, features a unique latticed wooden canopy providing shade and dynamic interplay between light and shadow. The garden's design seamlessly blends with nature, offering visitors an immersive experience. Additionally, the Nini Design Center provides innovative spaces for exhibitions and workshops.
name: Madeira Botanical Garden
address: 9060-345 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Funchal is the capital city of Portugal's Madeira archipelago. It's backed by hills, and known for its harbor, gardens and Madeira wine cellars. The centuries-old Funchal Cathedral, which mixes Gothic and Romanesque styles, is notable for its carved wooden ceiling. Fronting the harbor is the São Tiago Fortress, built in the 1600s. It now houses the Contemporary Art Museum, with a large collection of Portuguese works.
detail_description: Funchal, the capital city of Portugal's Madeira archipelago, is a charming destination backed by hills and renowned for its harbor, gardens, and Madeira wine cellars. The city boasts the centuries-old Funchal Cathedral with its unique mix of Gothic and Romanesque styles and the São Tiago Fortress, now home to the Contemporary Art Museum. Visitors can explore the city at their leisure, taking a cable car up to the botanical gardens and Monte Palace.
name: Funchal
address: Portugal

excerpt: Museum spotlighting the famous footballer Cristiano Ronaldo featuring his career history & trophies.
detail_description: The CR7 Museum, located in Madeira Island, is a dedicated space showcasing the remarkable career of renowned footballer Cristiano Ronaldo. Visitors can delve into his journey through an array of exhibits including photographs, videos, interactive displays, and an impressive collection of over a hundred individual and team trophies earned while playing for various teams.
name: CR7 Museum
address: Praça CR7, Av. Sá Carneiro 27, São Martinho, 9004-518 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Gothic-style, late-15th-century Catholic church with an ornate interior comprising 3 naves.
detail_description: Funchal Cathedral, a Gothic-style Catholic church dating back to the late 15th century, boasts an elaborate interior with three naves. The island of Madeira in the Atlantic Ocean is a stunning destination, abundant with vibrant flowers and aromatic fruits. Its volcanic landscape creates towering cliffs that offer breathtaking ocean views and conceal diverse wildlife and plant species. While Madeira is renowned for its tropical nature and botanical gardens, it also features well-developed cities with museums showcasing the island's rich history.
name: Funchal Cathedral
address: R. do Aljube, São Martinho, 9000-067 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Large, garden-like park with diverse trees, flower beds & walkways, plus a lake with ducks & swans.
detail_description: Santa Catarina Park is a spacious garden-like park in Madeira, featuring a variety of trees, flower beds, and walkways. Visitors can enjoy picnics by the lake while children have fun at the playground or feed ducks and swans. The park offers stunning views of Funchal Bay and provides a playroom for kids to engage in activities. Additionally, renting a bicycle to explore the large park or Funchal is an option.
name: Parque de Santa Catarina
address: Av. do Infante 18, São Martinho, 9000-015 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Sea & mountain views attract riders of this modern gondola running from Funchal to Monte.
detail_description: The Funchal Cable Car is a modern gondola that takes riders from Funchal to Monte, offering stunning views of the sea and mountains. The 20-minute ride provides a unique perspective of the city, with winding streets and clusters of houses resembling tiny models on a living map. At Monte, visitors can explore tropical gardens featuring exotic plants, flowers, and various animals.
name: Funchal Cable Car
address: Av. do Mar e das Comunidades Madeirenses, 9060-190 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Enormous, yellow-hued fort built in the 17th century to defend the city from attacks by pirates.
detail_description: Forte de São Tiago, a massive yellow fort constructed in the 17th century, was built to protect the city from pirate invasions. Originally erected in response to attacks by English, French, Algerian, and Turkish pirates drawn to Funchal's thriving sugar trade, the fortress now houses the Contemporary Art Museum. Visitors can explore its intricate passages and tower for breathtaking views of Funchal.
name: Forte de São Tiago
address: Tv. do Forte 8, 9060-123 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Lined with shops & cafes, the city's oldest street features doors painted by local & global artists.
detail_description: Rua de Santa Maria, located in the Old Town of Funchal, is a vibrant and historic street known for its colorful doors adorned with artwork by local and international artists. This pedestrianized lane is part of the Arte de Portas Abertas project, which aimed to revitalize the area after a tropical storm in 2010.
name: Rua de Santa Maria
address: 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Unique, modern museum with interactive exhibits of Madeira's history, plus a bistro with a terrace.
detail_description: Located in the heart of Funchal's Old Town, Madeira Story Centre is a unique and modern museum that offers interactive exhibits showcasing the history of Madeira. Visitors can take a virtual journey through time, experiencing significant events from the volcanic formation millions of years ago to historical figures like Prince Henry the Navigator and Churchill. The museum provides insights into Madeira's discovery, its volcanic origins, and its cultural heritage.
name: Madeira Story Centre
address: R. Dom Carlos I 27, 9060-051 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: A road reaches this 1,818-meter high peak, with a cafe & gift shop, that often looks down on clouds.
detail_description: Pico do Arieiro is one of the highest peaks in Madeira, reaching 1,818 meters above sea level. Visitors can drive up to this peak and enjoy a cafe and gift shop with stunning views that often overlook the clouds. The area offers a magical experience, especially during sunrise or sunset when the sky is painted in beautiful colors.
name: Pico do Arieiro
address: Portugal

excerpt: Samples & guided tours exploring Madeira wine production. barrel making & storage.
detail_description: Blandy's Wine Lodge offers samples and guided tours that provide an in-depth exploration of Madeira wine production, including barrel making and storage. Established in 1811, this family-run business provides a fascinating insight into the unique history and aging process of Madeira wines. Visitors can tour the warehouse filled with wooden barrels where the finest vintages are aged using the traditional canteiro method.
name: Blandy's Wine Lodge
address: Av. Arriaga 28, São Martinho, 9000-064 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Convent of Santa Clara, situated in Funchal, Portugal, is a must-see historical site dating back to the 15th century. Founded by Joao Goncalves da Camara, it offers a captivating insight into the region's religious and architectural legacy. The convent boasts remarkable Gothic and Manueline-style architecture with intricate details and beautiful archways.
name: Convent of Santa Clara
address: Calçada de Santa Clara 15, São Martinho, 9000-036 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Jardim Municipal do Funchal, also known as Jardim Dona Amelia, is a picturesque garden located in the heart of Funchal. It is adorned with towering trees, vibrant flowers, and various plants. The garden's privileged location offers a serene escape in the city center and features historical remnants like the Pedra de Armas from the former Convent of Sao Francisco.
name: Jardim Municipal do Funchal
address: R. Ivens 11, São Martinho, 9000-050 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Wine Tours Madeira offers a unique experience to explore the history and production of this fortified wine. Unlike port, Madeira undergoes the estufagem process and ages for years before bottling. A visit to Adegas de Sao Francisco provides a glimpse into the aging process with wines dating back to 1860. Blandys Wine Lodge in Funchal offers tours and tastings, allowing visitors to delve into 200 years of Madeira wine history.
name: Wine Tours Madeira
address: Rua de Santa Maria 63, 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Big, multi-level garden with exotic trees & flowers, ponds, African sculptures & a mineral museum.
detail_description: Monte Palace Tropical Garden, located in Madeira, is a stunning garden surrounding the former pleasure estate and luxury hotel Quinta Monte Palace. The garden boasts a diverse collection of exotic plants from around the world as well as rare native species from Madeira. Created by local entrepreneur Joe Berardo in the late 1980s, this garden features an array of trees, flowers, fountains, ponds, waterfalls, statues, and Japanese-themed gardens with pagodas and carp ponds.
name: Jardim Monte Palace Madeira
address: Caminho das Babosas 4 A, Monte, 9050-288 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: 500 years of art, ceramics, jewelry & antiques housed in an 18th-century villa in lush gardens.
detail_description: Quinta das Cruzes Museum is a historical gem located in an 18th-century villa surrounded by lush gardens. Once the residence of Funchal's second captain, this baroque-style quinta now houses a remarkable decorative art museum.
name: Quinta das Cruzes Museum
address: Calçada do Pico, nº1, 9000-206 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Bustling ocean getaway providing sand & pebble shores, restaurants & nearby shops & nightclubs.
detail_description: Praia Formosa, located in the west of Funchal, is a bustling ocean getaway with its black sand and pebble shores offering a striking view of the deep blue sea. As Madeira's largest free public beach, it consists of four stretches: Praia Nova, Praia Formosa, Praia dos Namorados, and Praia do Areeiro.
name: Praia Formosa
address: Portugal

excerpt: Monte is a civil parish in the municipality and a suburb of Funchal in the Portuguese archipelago of Madeira. Locally, the parish is also known as Nossa Senhora do Monte. The population in 2011 was 6,701, in an area of 18.59 km². Monte is located a few kilometres east of Funchal. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Monte, also known as Nossa Senhora do Monte, is a charming suburb of Funchal in Madeira, Portugal. With a population of 6,701 people living in an area of 18.59 km², this hilltop town offers breathtaking views of Funchal's white-washed houses and picturesque harbor. Visitors can take the cable car to reach Monte and explore its impressive church and gardens.
name: Monte
address: Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Praca do Município is a charming square featuring a pedestrianized area adorned with beautiful dark and light Batistini tiles arranged in wave patterns. At its heart, a striking fountain spire rises above an expansive overflowing basin, creating a captivating focal point. The square is encircled by streets where auto traffic and parking are permitted, making it easily accessible for visitors to explore and enjoy the surrounding area.
name: Praca do Município
address: São Martinho, 9000-082 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Marina do Funchal is a charming waterfront destination in the heart of Funchal, offering a picturesque setting for leisurely strolls and exciting excursions. The marina boasts wide promenades along the sea, lined with lush green spaces and Portuguese pavement walkways. Visitors can explore the area's numerous bars and upscale restaurants while taking in stunning views of the yachts moored at its 210-berth facility.
name: Marina do Funchal
address: São Martinho, Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Old Town | Bar & Lounge | is a captivating destination that invites you to explore the historic heart of Funchal, Portugal. As you stroll along its charming cobbled streets and squares, you'll encounter a blend of rich architectural heritage and vibrant street art that reflects Madeiran culture. Notable highlights include Rua da Santa Maria, where colorful murals celebrate local icons like fado singer Amalia and football star Cristiano Ronaldo.
name: Old Town | Bar & Lounge |
address: Tv. das Torres 6, 9060-314 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Igreja de São João Evangelista do Colégio do Funchal, also known as the College Church, is a significant religious site in Funchal. This 17th-century Baroque church was constructed by the Jesuits and boasts an intricate facade adorned with ornamental stonework and statues of saints. Inside, visitors are greeted by opulent gold leaf decorations covering the walls, columns, and altar.
name: Igreja de São João Evangelista do Colégio do Funchal
address: Largo do Colégio, São Martinho, 9000-000 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Dramatic, continuously showing 30-minute film showcasing the history & culture of Madeira.
detail_description: Açor,
name: Madeira Film Experience
address: nº1 | Marina Shopping, R. Conselheiro José Silvestre Ribeiro, São Martinho, 9000-060 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Câmara de Lobos is a municipality and town in the southern coast of the Portuguese island of Madeira, divided in 5 freguesias. A de facto suburb of the much larger capital city of Funchal, it is one of the larger population centres and an extension of the Funchal economy. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Câmara de Lobos is a charming and colorful fishing town located on the south-central coast of Madeira, just 9 km west of the capital city of Funchal. It serves as both a municipality and parish, offering a more traditional and laid-back atmosphere compared to its larger neighbor. While it may not have an abundance of activities, the town's relaxed vibe, scenic views, and ample photo opportunities make it an appealing place to stay for those seeking a quieter retreat.
name: Câmara de Lobos
address: Portugal

excerpt: Built 1529–1540, the city's first fortress includes an exhibit exploring the complex's history.
detail_description: Palácio de São Lourenço, a historical fortress dating back to the 15th century, is a significant landmark in Funchal. Originally serving as a residence for various captains and governors of Madeira Island, it was later restored and designated as a National Monument in 1943. Today, the palace houses a permanent exhibition that delves into its rich history and development as well as colonial architecture found throughout the city.
name: Palácio de São Lourenço
address: Av. Zarco, São Martinho, 9000-000 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Small casino offering slot machines & some table games, plus nightlife & dining options.
detail_description: Casino da Madeira, also known as O Casino do Funchal, is the only casino in the entire archipelago and is located just a 5-minute drive from the city center of Funchal. Designed by renowned architect Oscar Niemeyer, it boasts a unique and captivating architectural beauty. Visitors can enjoy slot machines and table games, as well as vibrant nightlife and dining options.
name: Casino da Madeira
address: Av. do Infante, São Martinho, 9004-513 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Modern cable car with vast panoramic views & connecting the lush Botanical Garden to Monte.
detail_description: The Funchal-Monte Cable Car is a modern transportation system offering vast panoramic views as it connects the lush Botanical Garden to Monte. This 15-minute journey covers a distance of 3,200 meters and rises 560 meters, providing breathtaking vistas of the city and its surroundings. With 42 cabins accommodating eight seats each, this eco-friendly mode of transport offers an exciting way to explore the hidden beauty of Funchal's hills while enjoying spectacular scenery.
name: Funchal-Monte Cable Car
address: Caminho das Voltas 15 Ilha da Madeira, 9060-329 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: This church is adorned with chandeliers, a revered statue of Our Lady of Monte & pieces of gold.
detail_description: The Igreja de Nossa Senhora do Monte, also known as the Church of Lady of Monte, is a significant pilgrimage site in Madeira. Every August, thousands of pilgrims gather here to celebrate Lady of Monte during one of the main festivities on the island. The church itself is adorned with chandeliers and houses a revered statue of Our Lady of Monte along with pieces of gold.
name: Igreja de Nossa Senhora do Monte
address: Rampa da Sacristia 1, Monte, 9050-285 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Curral das Freiras is a civil parish in the municipality of Câmara de Lobos in the Portuguese archipelago of Madeira. The population in 2011 was 2,001, in an area of 25.03 km². It is situated in the mountainous interior of the island. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Curral das Freiras, also known as the Valley of the Nuns, is a small parish located in the mountainous interior of Madeira. With a population of 2,001 people living in an area of 25.03 km², it offers stunning views and opportunities for hiking and exploration. Nearby attractions include Pico do Areeiro, the third highest peak in Madeira at 1818 meters altitude.
name: Curral das Freiras
address: Portugal

excerpt: Historic area with narrow cobbled streets lined with restaurant & bars, plus old merchant houses.
detail_description: Zona Velha, also known as the Old Town of Funchal, is a historic neighborhood characterized by its narrow cobbled streets and old merchant houses. This area is the oldest district in Funchal and showcases some of the city's earliest streets and buildings, some dating back to the 15th century.
name: Zona Velha do Funchal
address: Rua de Santa Maria 1, 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Viewpoint with a cafe & vistas sweeping over Funchal, the sea & rugged inland mountains.
detail_description: Pico dos Barcelos viewpoint is a must-visit spot in Madeira, offering sweeping vistas of Funchal, the sea, and the rugged inland mountains. Accessible by car or foot, this iconic vantage point provides a 360-degree view of the city. Visitors can enjoy a cafe on-site and take in the breathtaking scenery. It's recommended to visit with family and make use of nearby amenities such as free parking, restaurants, and even free toilets.
name: Pico dos Barcelos viewpoint
address: Urbanização Pico dos Barcelos 1, 9020-262 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Landscaped green space showcasing tropical plants in a hillside venue overlooking the ocean.
detail_description: Palheiro Gardens is a stunning hillside venue that offers breathtaking views of the ocean and showcases a variety of tropical plants. The gardens originated in the early 1800s when exotic trees from around the world were planted, and over time, more exotics were introduced, creating an impressive ensemble of gardens including the Main Garden, Sunken Garden, Ribeiro do Inferno, Rose Garden, and Ladys Garden.
name: Palheiro Gardens
address: Caminho da Quinta do Palheiro , 32 São Gonçalo, 9060-255 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Year-round gardens showcasing a wide variety of orchids & other exotic plants & flowers.
detail_description: Quinta da Boa Vista is a must-visit destination for nature enthusiasts, boasting year-round gardens with an impressive array of over 500 orchid varieties and other exotic plants and flowers. The estate, which has been meticulously cultivated for over two decades, offers breathtaking views of Funchal from its uphill location. Visitors praise the extensive collection of orchids and commend the expertise of the gardeners.
name: Quinta da Boa Vista
address: Rua do Lombo da Boavista 21, 9060-173 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled on the southern coast of Madeira, Doca do Cavacas is a hidden gem that perfectly blends relaxation and stunning natural beauty. This charming beach, also known as Poca do Gomes, lies conveniently between the Lido and Formosa beach in Funchal. With its inviting volcanic swimming pool and direct sea access, it offers breathtaking views of the Atlantic Ocean and Cabo Girao skywalk—the highest cliff in Europe.
name: Doca do Cavacas
address: Rua da Ponta da Cruz 66, 9000-250 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: UauCacau is not your typical restaurant, but it's a must-visit chocolate shop in Funchal. Founded by master chocolatier Tony Fernandes, this place offers an array of delectable chocolate truffles, cakes, and other sweet treats. With over 40 different flavors inspired by the island's products like banana, mango, passion fruit, and Madeira wine, UauCacau promises a unique culinary experience.
name: UauCacau
address: R. Q.Baixo 11, São Martinho, 9000-068 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Old Town is a charming dining spot with an incredible menu offering a variety of options at reasonable prices. The staff are friendly and helpful, providing excellent service and recommendations. Visitors praise the delicious food, generous portion sizes, and the welcoming atmosphere. It's recommended as a must-visit location for a memorable dining experience in Madeira.
name: Old Town
address: 9060-129 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Monte parish is home to the renowned Church of Lady of Monte, accessible via the iconic Madeira Cable Car. This church, constructed on the grounds of a 15th-century chapel and finalized in 1818, holds historical significance as the resting place of Charles of Habsburg, the final emperor of Austria who passed away in exile in Madeira in 1922.
name: Monte
address: Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Jesuit College of Funchal, also known as Colegio dos Jesuitas do Funchal, holds significant historical value and is a must-visit when in Funchal. Situated on the Town Hall Square, this 16th-century architectural masterpiece was initially located in the guesthouse Sao Sebastiao before moving to its current location. The college's stunning interior features remarkable sculptures and paintings, making it one of Madeira's most notable buildings.
name: Jesuit College of Funchal
address: R. dos Ferreiros Estrada, São Martinho, 9000-082 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: The 18th-century house museum of collector Frederico de Freitas is dedicated to the decorative arts.
detail_description: The House Museum of Frederico de Freitas in Funchal is a treasure trove of decorative arts and historical artifacts. The museum showcases the impressive collection of objects gathered by Madeiran collector Frederico Augusto de Freitas, including English-style furniture, paintings, pottery, and a remarkable assortment of glazed Portuguese tiles. Visitors can explore the romantic-style house where Dr.
name: House Museum of Frederico de Freitas
address: Calçada de Santa Clara nº7, São Martinho, 9000-036 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: This museum specializes in sacred art beginning in the Renaissance, with Flemish paintings & more.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Funchal, the Sacred Art Museum of Funchal is a treasure trove for art enthusiasts and history buffs alike. Housed in what was once the Bishops' Palace, this museum showcases an impressive collection of sacred art that spans from the Renaissance to the 19th century.
name: Sacred Art Museum of Funchal
address: R. do Bpo. 21, São Martinho, 9000-073 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Large, garden-like park with diverse trees, flower beds & walkways, plus a lake with ducks & swans.
name: Parque de Santa Catarina
address: Av. do Infante 18, São Martinho, 9000-015 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Madeira Explorers - Tourism Leisure Ltd offers a variety of tours, including the Lakes of Madeira walk and other popular routes like Fanal Assobiadores and Levada 25 Fontes. The experiences are well-organized, with punctual hotel pickups and comfortable transportation. The guides are friendly, knowledgeable, and create an enjoyable atmosphere for the participants. Despite some discrepancies between online descriptions and actual experiences, guests have found the tours to exceed their expectations.
name: Madeira Explorers - Tourism Leisure Ltd
address: Centro Comercial Lido, Estrada Monumental 284 Lj. 5, 1º Piso, São Martinho, 9004-541 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Madeira Island, the Art Center Caravel is a vibrant hub for art enthusiasts and casual visitors alike. Despite its modest exterior, this expansive center spans multiple floors, featuring an array of exhibition spaces that celebrate contemporary art from both local and international talents. Visitors can explore captivating paintings, sculptures, and installations by renowned artists such as Marcos Milewski and Anna Fedrova.
name: Art Center Caravel
address: Rua de Santa Maria 60, 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Funchal, the 3D Fun Art Museum is a delightful escape into a world where creativity and imagination reign supreme. Opened in 2019, this innovative museum boasts over 40 captivating scenarios that blend stunning 3D art with clever optical illusions. It's an ideal spot for visitors of all ages to engage with art in a playful way, allowing you to step right into the scenes and become part of the artwork itself.
name: 3D Fun art museum
address: R. do Surdo 24, São Martinho, 9000-223 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Collection of decorative arts amassed by a well-traveled individual, displayed in an 1800s house.
detail_description: Universo de Memórias João Carlos Abreu is a unique museum housed in an 1800s building, showcasing the extensive collection of decorative arts amassed by Joao Carlos Abreu, a well-traveled individual with diverse talents. The museum features over ten thousand pieces including books, ceramics, paintings, and bronze objects from around the world displayed across 14 rooms. Visitors can also enjoy a Tea House with free entrance on-site.
name: Universo de Memórias João Carlos Abreu
address: Calçada do Pico 4, 9000-206 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Holy Trinity Church, an English church built in 1822, features a distinctive neoclassical facade with imposing columns. Inside, visitors can admire a striking central dome and a mural depicting palm trees symbolizing Madeira's subtropical environment. The church is surrounded by a beautiful garden and offers a tranquil atmosphere for prayer. Additionally, it hosts classical concerts that are highly recommended for classical music enthusiasts.
name: Holy Trinity Church
address: R. do Quebra Costas 18, São Martinho, 9000-034 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Unpretentious museum about the area's history of electricity, with vintage tools in basic exhibits.
detail_description: The Museum of Electricity Casa da Luz in Funchal, Madeira is a museum dedicated to the history of electricity on the island. The museum has exhibits with vintage tools and equipment, as well as information about how electricity was used in Funchal and elsewhere in Portugal and Europe during the early 20th century. There is also an interactive section for children on the second floor. Admission is free for adults.
name: Museu de Electricidade Casa da Luz
address: R. Casa da Luz 2, 9000-061 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Imposing hilltop castle offering panoramic views of the city & sea, plus an adjacent cafe.
detail_description: The Fortaleza de São João Baptista do Pico, also known as the Fortress of Saint John the Baptist, is a historic landmark in Funchal, Portugal. Situated near the harbor, this 17th-century fortress played a vital role in protecting the island from pirate attacks. With its imposing stone walls, bastions, and a remarkable central tower, it offers panoramic views of the city and sea.
name: Fortaleza de São João Baptista do Pico
address: R. do Castelo 17, 9000-206 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Armazém do Mercado is a trendy and modern space in Funchal, offering a variety of shops with distinct products such as paintings, plants, and used paperback books. It's conveniently located near the famous Mercado dos Lavradores and is a perfect indoor attraction for all weather conditions. Visitors can explore different galleries showcasing various types of art at affordable prices. The place has a local artisan touch and offers unique souvenirs handmade by local artists.
name: Armazém do Mercado
address: R. Hospital Velho 28, 9060-129 Funchal, Portugal
